Attribution / references
------------------------
The ARM instruction ENCODINGS implemented here (both the Thumb/T32 and ARM/A32
states, plus the VFP, Advanced SIMD (NEON) and M-profile Vector Extension (MVE /
"Helium") surfaces) were learned from, and are credited to, the official Arm
Architecture Reference Manuals:

  * Arm(R) v8-M Architecture Reference Manual (DDI 0553) -- the M-profile (T32) base
    ISA plus the MVE, security, low-overhead-loop and scalar floating-point extensions.
  * Arm(R) Architecture Reference Manual, A-profile (DDI 0487) -- the A32/T32 shared
    encodings and the A-profile floating-point / Advanced SIMD instructions.

"Arm", "Thumb", "NEON" and "Helium" are trademarks of Arm Limited.

The implementation is validated by differential testing against the GNU
(arm-none-eabi-as / arm-none-eabi-objdump, GPL) and LLVM (llvm-mc, Apache-2.0 WITH
LLVM-exception) assemblers, used strictly as external test ORACLES -- their binaries
are neither bundled nor redistributed with this crate.

This crate has zero runtime dependencies and copies no third-party source.
